HEADWORD: Harderian
<hw>Har*de"ri*an</hw> <pr>(h⟦aum⟧r*d⟦emac⟧"r⟦icr⟧*⟦ait⟧n)</pr>,
<pos>a.</pos> <fld>(Anat.)</fld> <def>A term applied to a lachrymal
gland on the inner side of the orbit of many animals which have a third
eyelid, or nictitating membrane. See <cref>Nictitating membrane</cref>,
under <er>Nictitate</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hard-favored</ent>⟦br⟧
